org.hibernate.ogm.dialect.query.spi

Class BackendQuery<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.hibernate.ogm.dialect.query.spi.BackendQuery<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of query as understood by the underlying dialect implementation

    @Experimental(value="This contract is under active development, incompatible changes may occur in future versions.")
public class BackendQuery<T>
extends Object
    Represents a NoSQL query as to be executed via QueryableGridDialect.executeBackendQuery(BackendQuery, QueryParameters, TupleContext)

    The wrapped query object generally represents the query in the native form supported by a given datastore, e.g. a String in a native query syntax or an object-based query representation such as the DBObject-based query representation in the case of MongoDB.

    Author:
    Gunnar Morling
